00:12:14.993 --> 00:12:16.597
to each other in
the first place.

00:12:16.697 --> 00:12:17.766
- [Osaki] I know!

00:12:17.866 --> 00:12:19.903
But, I didn't think
the two of them

00:12:20.003 --> 00:12:21.874
were gonna end up in the sack.

00:12:21.974 --> 00:12:24.212
- So, you're telling me
you didn't know

00:12:24.312 --> 00:12:26.517
what kind of reputation
he had with women.

00:12:26.617 --> 00:12:27.384
- That isn't the point,

00:12:27.484 --> 00:12:30.457
I don't give a damn
about his bad reputation!

00:12:30.558 --> 00:12:33.898
- Then why are you so freaked
out about them being together?

00:12:33.998 --> 00:12:36.135
(sighs)

00:12:36.236 --> 00:12:39.275
- Why does Trapnest,
have to keep doing this?

00:12:39.375 --> 00:12:42.481
They're taking away everything
that's important to me.

00:12:42.582 --> 00:12:44.252
(gasps)
(music box starts playing)

00:12:44.352 --> 00:12:48.460
The thing is, I know Ren, and
Hachi, don't belong to me.

00:12:48.561 --> 00:12:50.330
They're people, not possessions,

00:12:50.430 --> 00:12:51.299
and it's totally wrong of me

00:12:51.399 --> 00:12:54.071
to even let myself
think of them like that.

00:12:54.171 --> 00:12:56.577
People can spend their time
together,

00:12:56.677 --> 00:12:58.881
but ultimately we're all alone.

00:12:58.981 --> 00:13:01.185
Everyone's got their own
life to live,

00:13:01.286 --> 00:13:04.726
and I know it's impossible
to make someone mine.

00:13:05.895 --> 00:13:07.699
But sometimes that realization

00:13:07.799 --> 00:13:10.203
just makes me feel
even more lonely.

00:13:13.176 --> 00:13:14.312
You know what worries me?

00:13:14.412 --> 00:13:17.886
I really was thinking of
Hachiko, as my pet puppy dog.

00:13:20.758 --> 00:13:22.194
I'm the worst.

00:13:22.294 --> 00:13:23.330
(clanking)

00:13:23.430 --> 00:13:24.533
(sips)

00:13:24.633 --> 00:13:26.002
(clanking)

00:13:26.102 --> 00:13:27.204
(sighs)

00:13:27.304 --> 00:13:29.676
(phone rings)
- Hmm?

00:13:29.776 --> 00:13:31.379
- Hmm.

00:13:31.479 --> 00:13:34.352
(Keypad beeps)

00:13:36.089 --> 00:13:37.358
Hmm.

00:13:37.458 --> 00:13:39.362
- Heh.

00:13:39.462 --> 00:13:41.533
I'm going straight
to work from here.

00:13:41.634 --> 00:13:44.005
Why don't you catch
a cab with me.

00:13:44.105 --> 00:13:47.244
That way you could talk this
over some more with Ren.

00:13:50.652 --> 00:13:52.488
(engine revving)

00:13:52.589 --> 00:13:54.693
- [Osaki] I'm sorry Yasu,

00:13:54.793 --> 00:13:58.333
I, sometimes I think I
depend on you too much,

00:13:58.433 --> 00:13:59.536
even though I know it.

00:13:59.636 --> 00:14:00.705
I keep doing it.

00:14:00.805 --> 00:14:01.472
- If you know you keep doing it

00:14:01.573 --> 00:14:04.445
then it's time to grow
up and fend for yourself.

00:14:04.546 --> 00:14:05.347
How am I gonna get a girlfriend,

00:14:05.447 --> 00:14:08.754
when I have you, calling me
at all hours of the night?

00:14:08.854 --> 00:14:09.823
- You're absolutely right.

00:14:09.923 --> 00:14:11.694
I'm gonna try my
hardest to grow up

00:14:11.794 --> 00:14:13.898
before you get back together
with Reira.

00:14:13.998 --> 00:14:15.000
- And what makes you think

00:14:15.100 --> 00:14:17.037
I should get back together
with Reira?

00:14:17.137 --> 00:14:20.344
- Because if fate has
anything to do with it,

00:14:20.444 --> 00:14:22.047
everything that's important
to me

00:14:22.147 --> 00:14:23.951
will be taken by Trapnest.

00:14:24.051 --> 00:14:26.322
- [Yasushi] I'm in the same
boat as you on that one.

00:14:26.422 --> 00:14:26.890
- Hmm?

00:14:26.991 --> 00:14:29.061
- First of all, my
girlfriend up and leaves me,

00:14:29.161 --> 00:14:31.366
so she can move to Tokyo
with the band.

00:14:31.466 --> 00:14:34.138
Next, they go and head
hunt my best friend.

00:14:34.238 --> 00:14:36.510
And then there's the
singer in my band.

00:14:36.610 --> 00:14:39.415
She's going out with the
guitar player from Trapnest.

00:14:39.516 --> 00:14:41.486
- (gasps) You're so right!

00:14:41.587 --> 00:14:44.458
How can I feel happy about
going to see the guitarist

00:14:44.559 --> 00:14:47.297
of a rival band in the
middle of the night?

00:14:47.398 --> 00:14:47.999
- Oh?

00:14:48.099 --> 00:14:49.836
So, you're happy being with Ren.

00:14:49.936 --> 00:14:51.439
That's good to know.

00:14:51.540 --> 00:14:53.243
- Maybe I should go home

00:14:53.343 --> 00:14:53.944
- Go see him.

00:14:54.045 --> 00:14:54.980
- (smacks) Damn it all.

00:14:55.080 --> 00:14:56.449
Why is it always like this?

00:14:56.550 --> 00:14:59.656
I bet this has got something
to do with Hachi's, demon lord,

00:14:59.756 --> 00:15:03.496
or maybe Trapnest is actually
an army of demon lords.

00:15:03.597 --> 00:15:04.933
- You know, it's hard to believe

00:15:05.033 --> 00:15:06.737
how much you and Ren, are alike.

00:15:06.837 --> 00:15:08.073
- Huh?

00:15:09.241 --> 00:15:10.678
- Before Ren, moved to Tokyo,

00:15:10.778 --> 00:15:12.014
I remember him saying the kind
of stuff

00:15:12.114 --> 00:15:13.984
you've been saying tonight.

00:15:15.755 --> 00:15:20.565
(somber music)

00:15:20.665 --> 00:15:23.537
- In the end, we are all alone.

00:15:23.637 --> 00:15:26.510
No matter how hard you
try or how close you get,

00:15:26.610 --> 00:15:29.583
it's impossible for two
people to become as one.

00:15:33.991 --> 00:15:36.062
- [Ren] I know it's impossible,

00:15:37.498 --> 00:15:41.072
but sometimes I really
wish that Nana, was mine.

00:15:41.172 --> 00:15:45.147
It's like, I want her
all for myself.

00:15:45.247 --> 00:15:48.253
That way I could just slip
her into my jacket pocket,

00:15:48.353 --> 00:15:50.858
and take her with me to
live in Tokyo.

00:15:50.958 --> 00:15:53.964
- Nah, she'd never fit
in your pocket.

00:15:55.133 --> 00:15:57.438
I know this might sound like
a crazy idea,

00:15:57.539 --> 00:15:59.676
but you could just
ask her to come with you.

00:15:59.776 --> 00:16:02.682
- (chuckles) Wouldn't
that be cool?

00:16:02.782 --> 00:16:04.218
I'll give it a try.

00:16:05.721 --> 00:16:07.324
- [Yasushi] Yeah, do it.

00:16:08.928 --> 00:16:12.936
(somber music continuing)

00:16:18.413 --> 00:16:21.385
- [Ren] You can live your
life however you want.

00:16:30.538 --> 00:16:33.476
(footsteps approaching)

00:16:33.577 --> 00:16:36.349
- I'd forgotten you can
see the ocean in Tokyo,

00:16:36.449 --> 00:16:37.552
I like it.

00:16:37.652 --> 00:16:40.925
- It's a pretty amazing
view, wanna move in?

00:16:44.265 --> 00:16:46.737
- Hmm, I'll think about it.

00:16:46.837 --> 00:16:49.175
(sighs)

00:16:51.880 --> 00:16:53.183
- [Hachiko] The next day,

00:16:53.283 --> 00:16:54.820
Takumi, ate nearly all the food

00:16:54.920 --> 00:16:56.957
I prepared the night before.

00:17:00.898 --> 00:17:02.602
And in the afternoon, he left,

00:17:02.702 --> 00:17:04.706
saying he had work to do.

00:17:05.741 --> 00:17:09.114
(slow piano music)

00:17:12.989 --> 00:17:14.993
I couldn't wait to tell Nana,
everything.

00:17:15.093 --> 00:17:17.866
I wanted to tell her
before all the happiness

00:17:17.966 --> 00:17:20.036
that I was feeling, faded away.

00:17:25.347 --> 00:17:27.117
Nana's, late getting home.

00:17:27.217 --> 00:17:28.587
She told me she didn't have
plans

00:17:28.687 --> 00:17:30.223
for anything special today.

00:17:30.323 --> 00:17:32.929
Maybe she's still over at Ren's,
place.

00:17:33.029 --> 00:17:35.535
But if Takumi, had to
leave to go to work,

00:17:35.635 --> 00:17:37.572
then so would Ren.

00:17:37.672 --> 00:17:39.308
- [Takumi] Well, even
when we get a day off,

00:17:39.408 --> 00:17:41.045
there's still lots to do.

00:17:41.145 --> 00:17:42.749
I'm sorry,

00:17:42.849 --> 00:17:44.451
I'll call you later.

00:17:46.255 --> 00:17:49.295
- Maybe he isn't working
after all.

00:17:49.395 --> 00:17:51.533
(whimpers) No, I have to
believe in him!

00:17:51.633 --> 00:17:53.904
I'm different from all
of the other girls.

00:17:54.004 --> 00:17:56.075
He trusts me 'cause I
understand him.

00:17:56.175 --> 00:17:58.346
(keypad beeping)

00:17:58.446 --> 00:18:01.587
Nana, when are you coming home?

00:18:02.421 --> 00:18:04.391
I've got lots to tell you.

00:18:05.895 --> 00:18:06.930
(doorbell rings)

00:18:07.030 --> 00:18:07.966
(gasps)

00:18:08.066 --> 00:18:09.201
(fast steps)

00:18:09.301 --> 00:18:13.376
(door opens)
Hey, welcome home!

00:18:13.476 --> 00:18:14.311
Ah.

00:18:17.886 --> 00:18:19.990
- Honey, I'm home.

00:18:20.090 --> 00:18:20.925
Isn't that how it goes?

00:18:21.025 --> 00:18:22.662
(laughing)

00:18:22.762 --> 00:18:24.265
- Sorry, Nobuo, it's you!

00:18:24.365 --> 00:18:27.271
I thought it was Nana.
(chuckles)

00:18:27.371 --> 00:18:29.709
- Ah, so Nana's, still out.

00:18:29.809 --> 00:18:30.377
- Mhm.

00:18:30.477 --> 00:18:32.782
I think she must be over at
Rem's, place.

00:18:32.882 --> 00:18:33.584
- Right?

00:18:33.684 --> 00:18:34.886
- Sorry, come on in.

00:18:34.986 --> 00:18:37.057
(footsteps)

00:18:37.157 --> 00:18:38.861
I was just sending Nana, a text.

00:18:38.961 --> 00:18:40.965
Do you want me to call her?

00:18:41.065 --> 00:18:42.535
- Uh, no,

00:18:42.635 --> 00:18:45.340
actually I came here to see you
Hachi.

00:18:46.375 --> 00:18:48.647
I need to talk, to you.

00:18:48.747 --> 00:18:49.883
- To me?

00:18:49.983 --> 00:18:50.585
(clank)

00:18:50.685 --> 00:18:53.791
- No, I don't need to
be drunk to say this!

00:18:55.026 --> 00:18:56.830
- What's going on?

00:18:56.930 --> 00:18:58.634
(sighs)

00:18:58.734 --> 00:19:00.270
Did something happen?

00:19:06.583 --> 00:19:08.721
(gasps)

00:19:12.227 --> 00:19:13.597
(smacks)
(sighs)

00:19:13.697 --> 00:19:15.433
- [Nobuo] I can't do it.

00:19:15.534 --> 00:19:16.970
- Can't do what?

00:19:17.070 --> 00:19:17.505
- [Nobuo] I'll come back later!

00:19:17.605 --> 00:19:18.741
- What the hell?
(bonking)

00:19:18.841 --> 00:19:19.509
- I should never have come.

00:19:19.609 --> 00:19:21.045
I can't compete with him.
(door opens)

00:19:21.145 --> 00:19:21.980
What was I thinking?

00:19:22.080 --> 00:19:23.182
- What are you talking about?

00:19:23.283 --> 00:19:24.919
Let me help you.

00:19:25.020 --> 00:19:26.923
- One of these days,
I'll show him.

00:19:27.024 --> 00:19:28.293
- Show who?

00:19:28.961 --> 00:19:29.796
- Takumi.

00:19:29.896 --> 00:19:32.702
(dramatic music)

00:19:32.802 --> 00:19:35.473
(footsteps)

00:19:37.010 --> 00:19:40.417
(crickets chirping)

00:19:43.691 --> 00:19:45.360
(footsteps approaching)

00:19:45.460 --> 00:19:45.628
(beeps)

00:19:45.728 --> 00:19:48.299
- [Messenger] You have two new
messages.

00:19:48.399 --> 00:19:49.769
(beeps)
(footsteps)

00:19:49.869 --> 00:19:51.506
- Yo Yasu, it's me Naoki!

00:19:51.606 --> 00:19:52.107
(thud)

00:19:52.207 --> 00:19:54.044
I just left a message on your
cell phone.

00:19:54.144 --> 00:19:55.413
It'd be great to see you
sometime.

00:19:55.514 --> 00:19:56.917
When are you free?
(clanking)

00:19:57.017 --> 00:19:58.486
I can bring Reira, with me.

00:19:58.587 --> 00:20:01.927
Ha ha, call me, see ya.
(crinkling)

00:20:02.027 --> 00:20:03.496
(beep)

00:20:03.597 --> 00:20:04.799
- What's with everyone these
days?

00:20:04.899 --> 00:20:06.435
(lighter ignites)
- My name's Kawano,

00:20:06.536 --> 00:20:08.339
I'm calling from Gaia Music.

00:20:08.439 --> 00:20:10.611
We've had a chance to
review your demo tape,

00:20:10.711 --> 00:20:11.513
and your live video.

00:20:11.613 --> 00:20:15.153
We'd like to set up a meeting
with you as soon as possible.

00:20:15.253 --> 00:20:18.727
(ambient rock music)

00:20:20.230 --> 00:20:22.902
(shuffling)

00:20:24.038 --> 00:20:27.177
- Are you serious, you sure?

00:20:29.314 --> 00:20:32.354
- [Cashier] That comes
to 1,215 yuan please.

00:20:32.454 --> 00:20:34.859
- Here well, why don't you
let me take care of that.

00:20:34.959 --> 00:20:36.530
(smacks)
- It's my stuff.

00:20:37.097 --> 00:20:39.769
(shuffling)

00:20:41.740 --> 00:20:43.142
(thud)

00:20:43.242 --> 00:20:45.848
- Mind if we throw this in too?

00:20:45.948 --> 00:20:48.754
(gasps)

00:20:48.854 --> 00:20:52.528
- [Hachiko] Hey Nana, our
lives were so intertwined,

00:20:52.628 --> 00:20:56.703
but still, I didn't
understand you at all.

00:20:58.339 --> 00:21:00.845
I had no idea I was hurting you.

00:21:01.847 --> 00:21:04.184
Please forgive me.

